d-white illustrations and two maps.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLiterature, MedievalxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aNarration (Rhetoric)xHistoryyTo 1500. 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 0aPower (Social sciences). 0aRhetoric, Medieval. 0aSocial historyyMedieval, 500-1500. 0aWomen and literaturexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aWomen and literaturezEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomenxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 500-1500. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies.1 aErler, Mary C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKowaleski, Maryanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172395740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501723957423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501723957/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles